^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, lets do the auction first. I would open 2S with duffer's hand, but very few others would, so pass is fine. 1C and 1D are fine. The problem with 2S is duffer's hand is a bit strong to bid it and her points are outside the spade suit. A weak jump shift is typically around 3 points. We might have game if I have 4 spades and a 20 count or so. Bidding 2S precludes us from finding it. Now, granted the 1D bid makes your Q of diamonds less valuable.|
PG| ***** 18 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at| My choice would be 1S. If you count your Starting Points you have 5 HCP + 2 length points = 7. Even if you deduct 1 for the Q of diamonds, you still have 6. Then, roberta should bid 3D over 2S. It is very clear. Remember the law of total tricks. Always follow it. You have 9 card fit, so bid at the 3 level. In fact, roberta is closer to a 3C limit raise than a pass, but I think 3D is just right. If roberta bids 3D then I bid 3S, which is what we should make.|
